Firstly, I want to say thank you for your content and inspirational videos, since the very beginning. I've been a huge fan since your very first, humble beginnings but I want to say the following to you out of love.

I cannot believe you would turn your world upside down, risk not only your lives, your son's life, your boats safety to ferry the ungrateful Greta Thunberg, who's from my home country (makes me ashamed to be born a Swedish Viking sometimes, but I won't let her ruin more than her own life) to her 'Global Warming' summit (or whatever they wanna call it now haha). I have to say that I agree with many other yachtsmen who live by the creed of 'no deadlines' and not moving your home and family to the very inhospitable Mediterranean during winter, just for this publicity stunt.

I wish you all the very best for your lovely family, and I hope God will keep you all safe, and be with you wherever your destinations end up. I hope you'll return to focusing on being grateful for what you have, your family, your home and your lives.

Two different people complained that Greta was transported on a "yacht" and it cost more CO2 to do that than fly (because they seem to think it's some huge thing like the show "Below Deck", I assume).
